<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Virtual Pathology Museum</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="header">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <div class="logo">Virtual Pathology Museum</div>
            <div class="auth-buttons">
                <% if (user) { %>
                    <div class="user-info">
                        <span>Welcome, <%= user.email %></span>
                        <form action="/logout" method="POST" style="display: inline;">
                            <button type="submit" class="logout-btn">Logout</button>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                <% } else { %>
                    <a href="/login" class="btn btn-login">Login</a>
                    <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-signup">Sign Up</a>
                <% } %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title">VIRTUAL PATHOLOGY MUSEUM</h1>
        
        <div class="content">
            <p class="welcome-text">
                Welcome to our <span class="highlight-blue">VIRTUAL PATHOLOGY MUSEUM</span>! You will find both 
                <span class="highlight-blue">virtual pathology pots</span> and 
                <span class="highlight-blue">virtual microscopy slides</span> here.
            </p>

            <p>
                Explore our virtual pathology pots - you can rotate and magnify them - almost as if you are holding them in your hands! 
                Click on the bottom left orange arrow to open up the label menu, so that you can view annotations.
            </p>

            <p>
                Here are simple instructions on <a href="#">how to manoeuvre the Virtual Pots</a>.
            </p>

            <p>
                Many more features are available - Clinical vignettes, Macroscopic descriptions, Microscopic correlates and even unique 
                radiologic images enabling you to "see through" the pots!
            </p>

            <p>
                View this in tandem with <a href="#">Pathology Demystified</a>, and test your observational skills before you reveal the annotations!
            </p>

            <p>
                <span class="highlight-red">For alternative microscopy slides, click</span> <a href="#">here</a>
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="cards-section">
            <div class="cards-grid">
                <div class="card blue-card">
                    <div class="card-image">
                        <img src="/uv2.png" alt="Intestinal gangrene">
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Intestinal gangrene</h3>
                        <div class="card-links">
                            <a href="/description/intestinal-gangrene">Description</a>
                            <a href="/video/intestinal-gangrene">Video</a>
                            <a href="/model/intestinal-gangrene">3D Model</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card orange-card">
                    <div class="card-image">
                        <img src="/uv1main.png" alt="Leiomyoma">
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Leiomyoma</h3>
                        <div class="card-links">
                            <a href="/description/leiomyoma">Description</a>
                            <a href="/video/leiomyoma">Video</a>
                            <a href="/model/leiomyoma">3D Model</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="cards-grid">
                <div class="card blue-card">
                    <div class="card-image">
                        <img src="/uv1.png" alt="Acute appendicitis">
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Acute appendicitis</h3>
                        <div class="card-links">
                            <a href="/description/acute-appendicitis">Description</a>
                            <a href="/video/acute-appendicitis">Video</a>
                            <a href="/model/acute-appendicitis">3D Model</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card orange-card">
                    <div class="card-image">
                        <img src="/uv22.png" alt="Lipoma">
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Lipoma</h3>
                        <div class="card-links">
                            <a href="/description/lipoma">Description</a>
                            <a href="/video/lipoma">Video</a>
                            <a href="/model/lipoma">3D Model</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>